:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Halloween 5
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<storeon "gwylan_clothes_halloween">>

It all passes by in a blur. One moment, you're a mummy defending your tomb. The next, a silent scarecrow standing in eternal vigil.
You're a skeleton playing its ribs like a xylophone, then a pumpkin in a patch.
<br><br>

With a final twirl, Gwylan redresses you in your original clothes. You're both panting from all the movement. You can't deny that you had a lot of fun, though. <<stress -6>><<trauma -20>><<lstress>><<lltrauma>>
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"D-did you enjoy that?" you ask. "Was there anything wrong with the costumes?"
	<<case "bratty">>
		"Done playing dressup with me?" you ask. "Were the costumes all to your liking?"
	<<default>>
		"Did you inspect me enough?" you ask. "Did the costumes all measure up?"
<</switch>>
<br><br>

"R-right. Costumes," <<he>> stammers, before giving you a big smile.
"Anything can be a costume. I think what someone defines as a costume says a lot about them. It's an opportunity for raw self-expression.
Even if you're unrecognisable, you're showing off an intimate part of yourself. Like being inside-out." <<He>> giggles. "Maybe that's why it's so scary to some people."
<br><br>

<<He>> pats you on the head. "Thanks for indulging me." <<gyearning>>
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

