	<<set $daily.gwylan.traumaTalk to true>>
	You tell Gwylan that it appeared after some strange occurrences involving an unusual arcade cabinet. About how the cabinet wasn't always there, and each time you played it, something strange followed.
	You finish the story with how you were nearly kidnapped by some strange people, but woke up back in your own room. You tell Gwylan that the machine simply vanished after that.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> blinks at you. "How much do you remember of the kidnapping?" <<he>> asks bluntly.
	<br><br>

	You explain that you remember seeing a factory, maybe the one on Elk street, and the smell of the colour pink. You don't remember much else.
	<br><br>

	Gwylan sighs. "Those memories probably aren't coming back, but that might be for the better. For your sake." <<He>> brightens up a bit. "Don't feel bad. My own curiosity has gotten the better of me plenty, and I've paid the price a fair few times."
<</if>>
<br><br>

