:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Pumpkin 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("pumpkin")>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	You tell Gwylan that you found it around Halloween.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> nods. "I'm not sure what else I was expecting."
<<else>>
	"This showed up after I learned how to cook. I think. That's the only correlation I can think of."
	<br><br>

	<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
		<<His>> fox ears perk up.
	<</if>>
	"Ooh, what can you make?"
	<br><br>

	You pause and think.
	<<set _foodsMentionedList to Object.values(setup.plants).filter(food => V.plants[food.name]?.recipe)>>
	"Let's see... <<recipe_name _foodsMentionedList.pluck().name "article">>, <<recipe_name _foodsMentionedList.pluck().name "article">>, <<recipe_name _foodsMentionedList.pluck().name "article">>, <<recipe_name _foodsMentionedList.pluck().name "article">>, <<recipe_name _foodsMentionedList.pluck().name "article">>..."
	You recount all the recipes you know to the best of your ability. Gwylan looks impressed.
	<br><br>

	"I know how to cook up a few things myself, although I specialise a bit. I prefer function over form. What about you?"
	<br><br>

	<<if $avery_mansion and $avery_mansion.food?.name isnot "none">>
		<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
			<<if $avery_fate isnot "fallen" and $avery_fate isnot "kicked">>
				You shift side to side. "Avery is very particular about what <<nnpc_he "Avery">> wants to eat every night."
				<br><br>

				<<He>> gives you an understanding smile.
				<<if $avery_fate>>
					"Well, you had a chance to be free from that. If you ever need a place to hide from that big baby, you're always welcome here."
				<<elseif $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
					"You'll be free from <<nnpc_him "Avery">> soon."
				<<else>>
					"If that kind of life isn't agreeing with you, then we need to redouble our efforts to find the bones. I can't have my best customer getting thrashed around for letting the roast sit for thirty seconds too long."
				<</if>>
			<<else>>
				You shift side to side. "Avery was very particular about what <<nnpc_he "Avery">> wanted to eat every night."
				<br><br>

				<<He>> frowns. "I'm sorry to hear that, but I'm glad you're free from <<nnpc_him "Avery">>."
			<</if>>
		<<else>>
			<<if $avery_fate isnot "fallen" and $avery_fate isnot "kicked">>
				Your mind turns to Avery. "Yes. There's someone I know who's particular about what <<nnpc_he "Avery">> wants to eat every night."
				<br><br>

				<<He>> gives you an understanding smile. "Picky partners, I know all about that. Food is a wonderful way to see the best and worst of someone."
			<<else>>
				Your mind turns to Avery. "I was with someone who was very particular about what <<nnpc_he "Avery">> wanted for dinner every night. That relationship didn't work out, though." You pause. "For <<nnpc_him "Avery">>, at least."
				<br><br>

				<<He>> frowns. "I'm sorry to hear that, but it sounds like you were too good for <<nnpc_him "Avery">>."
			<</if>>
		<</if>>
	<<else>>
		You recount some of your kitchen mishaps. Gwylan lends a patient ear and a warm smile all the while.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> leans back. "Maybe I'll spirit you away to my kitchen some time<<if $worn.upper.name is "pumpkin dress">>, little pumpkin<</if>>. I could certainly use the help."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

