:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Valentines Agree
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"There's more to live for," you say. "Love doesn't have to be romantic. Romance isn't all that important."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"It's a waste of time," you say. "I don't know how anyone can get caught up in romance in a life like this."
	<<default>>
		"There's more important things to worry about," you say. "Like not being sold off into slavery. Romance isn't important."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan winces, but smiles. "I'm sorry. Others shouldn't think like I do. Still, there's comfort in knowing I'm not alone." <<He>> returns to the counter without another word, tossing the
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
	the rose
<<else>>
	the broken stem of the rose
<</if>>
aside.
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Valentines Wrong
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"Y-you're wrong," you say. "Life isn't that miserable."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"You're not the only one that life has chewed up and spat out. You need to learn to see the good in the bad."
	<<default>>
		"No, you're wrong. Life's not that miserable," you say.
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<He>> looks to you with surprise. <<He>> opens <<his>> mouth to speak, but you cut <<him>> off.
<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"If it wasn't for the people I love, I would have given up a long time ago. S-sure, this town takes its toll, but...
	<<case "bratty">>
		"If it wasn't for the people that love me, I wouldn't still be here. Sure, this hellhole is pure misery, but...
	<<default>>
		"If it wasn't for the relationships I've formed, I wouldn't still be kicking. Sure, this town is a horrible place, but...
<</switch>>
it could be worse. We could be suffering in it alone."
<br><br>

A long moment of silence passes. Gwylan's fists clench, but <<he>> chuckles under <<his>> breath. "Misery loves company," <<he>> whispers.
<br><br>

<<He>> slowly turns to you. "I don't expect anyone else to understand, but my troubles are mine alone. I shouldn't have shared them. It was inappropriate, and a moment of weakness."
<<He>> gives you a half-forced smile. "Just forget about this, please." <<He>> returns to the counter.
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
