:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("loincloth")>><<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("eden_known")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
<<set $daily.gwylan.traumaTalk to true>>
You tell Gwylan about your time with Eden, and how <<nnpc_he "Eden">> must have been so lonely.
<br><br>

<<He>> looks surprised. "The <<= C.npc.Eden.title>>. You've gotten close with <i><<nnpc_him "Eden">></i>. <<nnpc_He "Eden">> stops by for supplies sometimes. Scrap fabric, burn ointment, the like." There's a peculiarity in <<his>> voice.
<br><br>

"That likely sounded rude, but I... hope you know who you've made bedfellows with. <<nnpc_He "Eden">>'s ravaged this forest's ecosystem.
<<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> well-built, but there's no way one <<nnpc_gender "Eden">> can eat as much as <<nnpc_he "Eden">> kills. It's wasteful and careless."
Gwylan walks around you, towards one of the forest shop's windows. <<He>> gazes out wistfully, as if looking for something that should be there.
<br><br>

"The children of the animals <<nnpc_hes "Eden">> killed, the ones that were never conceived, should be running free in our forest today.
There's a generational gap in the population because of people like <<nnpc_him "Eden">>. One <<nnpc_gender "Eden">>'s empty hatred reverberating its consequences forever.
Perhaps <<nnpc_he "Eden">> feels the forest wronged <<nnpc_him "Eden">> for..."
<br><br>

Gwylan shakes <<his>> head. "No. Those aren't my burdens to share. I'm certain you already know. If <<nnpc_his "Eden">> feelings for you are true, surely <<nnpc_hes "Eden">> told you."
Gwylan's gaze is provocative, as if <<he>> knows that Eden hasn't told you anything of the sort.
<br><br>

<<link [[Defend Eden calmly|Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Defend Eden angrily|Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Agree|Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden 2]]>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Stay silent|Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden 2]]>><<set $phase to 4>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Eden 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"I-I'm sure <<nnpc_he "Eden">> isn't doing it to be a bad person," you say. "I know it. <<nnpc_hes "Eden">> a good person deep down."
		<<case "bratty">>
			"Try walking a mile in <<nnpc_his "Eden">> shoes. Not everyone has the luxury of thinking about it as deeply as you do. Some people need to survive, regardless of morals."
		<<default>>
			"Fighting to survive doesn't make someone evil. <<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> doing what <<nnpc_he "Eden">> has to."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan scoffs. "There's survival, and there's <<nnpc_him "Eden">>. Morality has no stake in it, it's a simple fact of numbers. <<nnpc_He "Eden">> kills too much, and too often."
<<elseif $phase is 2>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"Y-you're wrong!" you shout, catching Gwylan off guard. "You don't know what <<nnpc_hes "Eden">> been through either! B-but you can't fake the kind of pain and loneliness <<nnpc_hes "Eden">> in. I see it in <<nnpc_his "Eden">> eyes every night. What could you possibly know about <<nnpc_him "Eden">>?"
		<<case "bratty">>
			"What the hell do you know?" you shout, catching Gwylan off guard. "Cooped up in this stuffy shop all day, you're not much different. How do you even know <<nnpc_him "Eden">>?"
		<<default>>
			"You're wrong!" you shout, catching Gwylan off guard. "You don't really know anything about <<nnpc_him "Eden">>, do you? How could you possibly understand <<nnpc_him "Eden">>?"
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan says nothing at first, merely taking a deep breath. <<His>> gaze on you doesn't change.
	<br><br>

	"I know enough. If you kill a mother fox, her kits will starve. You may forget the simple act, but the forest remembers. Forever.
	<<nnpc_His "Eden">> crimes are etched on every tree, with every bullet <<nnpc_he "Eden">> leaves carelessly strewn in the dirt for something to choke on."
<<elseif $phase is 3>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"<<nnpc_Hes "Eden">>... scary," you say. "So scary that I've become afraid of being away from <<nnpc_him "Eden">>."
		<<case "bratty">>
			"<<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> a pain," you agree. "<<nnpc_He "Eden">> thinks <<nnpc_he "Eden">> can take whatever <<nnpc_he "Eden">> wants, no matter how much it tries to run."
		<<default>>
			"<<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> difficult," you agree. "Selfish, even. No matter how much I try to get away, <<nnpc_he "Eden">> always chases me."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan smiles at you. "If a <<= C.npc.Eden.title>> can aim, <<nnpc_he "Eden">> will shoot. It's best to scurry away. I'm glad you understand that. If you ever need a place to hide, you're always welcome here."
<<else>>
	You stay silent. Gwylan frowns. "You're fond of <<nnpc_him "Eden">>. Perhaps you can change <<nnpc_him "Eden">> for the better, some day. But I have my doubts."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> looks away from you again, and sighs. "<<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> a victim, too, though. The forest has started to reflect <<nnpc_his "Eden">> hatred. Responding to a threat from within.
Becoming something ugly to survive. Becoming more dangerous. Does it sound familiar? <<nnpc_Hes "Eden">> part of a hopeless cycle, refusing to compromise. A self-fulfilling prophecy.
Perhaps we deserve each other."
<br><br>

<<He>> returns to the counter. "I won't hold it against you."
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Wolves
