:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Holy Stole
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("holy_stole")>>
You show Gwylan the holy stole.
<br><br>

<<He>> snickers. "You're definitely not supposed to have that. How did you find it?"
<br><br>

You explain that you found it after being very vigilant in your obligations to the temple, prompting Gwylan to briefly frown.
<br><br>

"I hope you're not losing yourself in them."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

<!-- Pendant trio -->

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Pendant
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("pendant")>>
You show Gwylan the three pendants.
<br><br>

"The trio is complete," <<he>> says. "It's always three. Urges, chastity, and purges. Conception, birth, and motherhood. Everyone, you, and the world under your feet." <<He>> hangs all three together, letting them overlap.
"The Children, the Cloister, and nobody." <<He>> frowns.
<br><br>

"It's a shame how much has been lost with time. Burned by those who seek to erase history so we'll be doomed to repeat it."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Holy Pendant
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("holy_pendant")>>
You show Gwylan the holy pendant.
<br><br>

"I believe it's made of brass," <<he>> says, weighing it in <<his>> hands. "Not just plated, either. It's heavier than it looks. It's a common ornament for the religious types, but I'm curious as to why you found it here."
<br><br>

You explain that you found it after finding the soup kitchen, which makes Gwylan smile.
<br><br>

"That's the kind of work the cloister should be doing more of." <<He>> starts to whirl the pendant by the cord, making the air whip around it. "You could really hurt someone with this if you threw it."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Stone Pendant
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("stone_pendant")>>
You show Gwylan the stone pendant. <<His>> eyes go wide, and <<he>> snatches it from your grasp.
<br><br>

<<He>> stares at it as if it would vanish when <<he>> next blinks. "Where did you find this?" <<he>> asks intently.
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I-it was lost in a crack at the temple," you say. "Is it really that impressive?"
	<<case "bratty">>
		"It was just jammed in a crack, somewhere in the temple," you say. "What's with the staring? It's just a shaped rock."
	<<default>>
		"I found it in the temple, lost in a crack," you say. "Is it really all that special?"
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<He>> huffs. "It's history. History that was erased. I didn't think there were any left." <<He>> hesitantly hands it back to you. "If you found this, it belongs with you."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Dark Pendant
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("dark_pendant")>>
You show Gwylan the dark pendant.
<br><br>

<<He>> shivers as <<he>> cautiously reaches for it. "How did you come across this?" <<He>> seems lost in it.
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I-it was in the loft in my home," you say. "At the orphanage. S-some of the orphans got bold enough to go somewhere Bailey forbade us from. Then it showed up here."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"It was in the loft at the orphanage," you say. "We got bold enough to go somewhere our 'guardian' wouldn't dare. Now it's here, for whatever reason."
	<<default>>
		"It was in the loft of the orphanage," you say. "A place our guardian wouldn't normally let us go. Then it showed up here."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<His>> hand clenches, prompting <<him>> to take a deep breath. "<<nnpc_Hes "Bailey">> haunted." <<He>> shakes <<his>> head. "Obsessed. Only ruin lies at the end of this road. Blood can't pay for blood, and the snake's hunger will lead it to devour its own tail."
<br><br>

Gwylan becomes unresponsive for a few minutes, looking down in shame. <<He>> refuses to comment any further.
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

<!-- Museum -->

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Historic
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("historic")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
You walk through the shop with Gwylan, browsing the collection of historic clothing and armour.
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"Th-this place is kind of like the museum," you say. "I'm sure Winter would like to have some of these."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"Do you think you're stepping on Winter's toes, keeping all this here?" you ask.
	<<default>>
		"I think Winter would want some of these items," you say. "At the museum."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan smiles at you. "<<nnpc_Hes "Winter">> made some offers, but I'm afraid I'm a bit too selfish to donate any of this. The shop wouldn't like it either."
<<He>> thinks for a moment. "You should accompany me to the museum some time, though."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Museum Rags
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("museum_rags")>>
You show Gwylan the rags.
<br><br>

"Those are just ripped scraps of cloth," <<he>> says. "They shouldn't be out in the shop. I keep trying to get rid of them, but they always show up again."
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"A-actually, these showed up after I helped Winter at the museum," you explain. "I demonstrated some... torture methods with <<nnpc_him "Winter">>."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"Actually, these showed up after I helped Winter demonstrate <<nnpc_his "Winter">> torture obsession over at the museum," you explain.
	<<default>>
		"No, actually, these showed up after I helped Winter with some demonstrations over at the museum," you explain.
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
	<<His>> fox ears twitch at the mention of Winter.
<<elseif ["revealed", "visible"].includes(_gwylanTF.ears) and $gwylanSeen.includes("hat_found")>>
	<span class="pink">You swear you see the fox ears on <<his>> hat twitch at the mention of Winter.</span>
	<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("gwylan_ears")>>
<</if>>
<<He>> immediately perks up. "We're acquainted, Winter and I. <<nnpc_He "Winter">> visits the shop every now and then. <<nnpc_He "Winter">>'s bought these useless rags from me, too.
I don't know why. <<nnpc_He "Winter">> could use any old scraps of cloth, but <<nnpc_he "Winter">> insists on using these."
<br><br>

You think you see the briefest hint of resentment in Gwylan's face as <<he>> looks down at the rags, but you might have imagined it.
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Vintage
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("vintage")>>
You show Gwylan the vintage suits.
<br><br>

<<He>> stares for a moment. "That looks like something my grand<<father>> would wear." <<He>> dusts off the shoulders of one of them. "They could really use a good dry-cleaning. How did you come across these?"
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"M-my history teacher told me a story from <<nnpc_his "Winter">> childhood. About the blitz. This showed up here after that," you explain.
	<<case "bratty">>
		"My history teacher droned on about a story from <<nnpc_his "Winter">> childhood, and how <<nnpc_he "Winter">> saw the blitz first-hand. This showed up here after that," you explain.
	<<default>>
		"My history teacher told me a story about the blitz. <<nnpc_He "Winter">> was a child affected by it. These suits showed up here after that," you explain.
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan nods along. "That sounds like the correct time period these would have been worn in." <<He>> stares down at the suits again before hanging them back up. "The Blitz left many broken families behind. Everybody was scared. Lost. Loved ones were dying. Children were getting traded, sometimes for food. Sometimes in the desperate hope they'd have a safer life elsewhere."
<br><br>
<<He>> tenses up, staring out one of the shop's windows. "I've heard about it second-hand, too. Winter teaches that war is diplomacy by other means. That it's how nations get what they want when words fail. That never felt right to me. All the people who get hurt, and hurt others because they're hurting, it's just a perpetual cycle of violence. When is enough finally enough? Why do people have to be chips in another's game? I can't stand the thought of it. Especially when it's children being held ransom." <<He>> looks back to you. "We don't purchase death, so why do we spend life? How did something so sacred become so easy to throw away?"
<br><br>
<<He>> returns to the counter, and blushes after a moment of silence. "Sorry about that. I don't know when to shut my mouth sometimes."
<br><br>
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("cafe_opening")>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"H-hold on," you start, remembering something. "Didn't I see you wearing this at the grand opening of the cafe?"
		<<case "bratty">>
			"Hey, wait a minute," you start, remembering something. "Why were you wearing this at the cafe's grand opening?"
		<<default>>
			"Wait a minute," you start, remembering something. "I saw you wearing this at the grand opening of the cafe."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<His>> blush deepens. "I couldn't find anything else in the shop to wear that day."
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Chain Tunic
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("chain_tunic")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
You show Gwylan the chain tunic.
<br><br>

Before you can say anything, <span class="red"><<he>> rips it out of your hands</span>. "That's not for sale!" <<he>> says anxiously, hugging it close to <<his>> chest.
<br><br>

<<His>> eyes dart around the tunic, inspecting it for damage. You notice a large rip in the skirt, but it doesn't look new. The whole set looks meticulously cared for, each chain polished to keep rust from forming.
Gwylan slowly becomes less frantic, until <<he>> lets out a sigh of relief. "I'm sorry. This is my most prized item. The shop has replicas, and this shouldn't have been out with them."
<br><br>

<<He>> smiles wistfully at it. "It's the oldest thing in my collection. Armour like this was worn by monks and nuns in darker times." <<He>> points you to the replicas.
You can't tell the difference between them and the original, other than the colours and lack of damage.
<br><br>

You look back to Gwylan. <<His>> face is buried in the tunic, and <<his>> eyes are closed.
<br><br>

You decide to give <<him>> a moment before returning to the counter.
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

<!-- Special Events -->

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Foreign School
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("foreign_school")>>
You show Gwylan the serafuku, and the other foreign school clothes.
<br><br>

"Those are cute," <<he>> says. "The style of a sailor became popular as school attire overseas at some point. How did you find them?"
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I found them on my headteacher's desk," you start. "Along with a lot of... awful pictures of students."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"They were on the headteacher's desk," you say. "Along with some disgusting pictures of the other students."
	<<default>>
		"I found them on the headteacher's desk," you say. "Along with a lot of incriminating evidence involving pictures of students."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<His>> nose scrunches. "Someone using their position to exert control over their peers. A tale as old as time. Have you told anyone about it?"
<br><br>

<<if $headblackmailed is 1 and $headpolice isnot 1>>
	You shake your head. "I got something I wanted out of it, though."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan smiles. "Good. I hope you made them feel what it's like to be helpless and pressured. Sometimes, we need to make our own justice."
<<elseif $headpolice is 1>>
	You nod. "I gave it to the police."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan smiles. "Good. I doubt they'll do anything about it without a little push, though. If, hypothetically, they just so happened to have some other crimes to look into, the evidence you gave them might just get expedited." <<He>> winks at you.
<<else>>
	You shake your head. "I don't know what to do with it."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan puts <<his>> hand to <<his>> chin. "If you want to take justice into your own hands, you could use it as leverage."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Brothel
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("brothel")>>
You show Gwylan the belly dancer's set and harem set.
<br><br>

"How unusual," <<he>> says. "What in the world have you been up to?"
<br><br>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"I had to make a deal with the brothel owner," you say. You shuffle your feet. "I need money.<<if $robinpaid gte 1>> Someone is depending on me for it.<</if>>"
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"I need money," you say bluntly. "So I made a deal with the <<nnpc_gender "Briar">> who runs the brothel.<<if $robinpaid gte 1>> It isn't just about me anymore.<</if>>"
<<else>>
	"I need money<<if $robinpaid gte 1>> to help a friend<</if>>, so I made a deal with the <<nnpc_gender "Briar">> who owns the brothel," you explain.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Gwylan takes the clothing from you. <<He>> rubs the thin fabric between <<his>> thumb and forefinger. "Disguises can be armour against the world," <<he>> says. "Perhaps the shop wants to protect you.<<if V.gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>> I know I do.<</if>>"
<br><br>

<<He>> folds the sets. "If you ever need a place of comfort, my door is open, dear."
