:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Hookah
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("hookah")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
You show Gwylan the esoteric spectacles.
<br><br>

<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
	<<His>> fox ears twitch.
<<elseif _gwylanTF.ears is "revealed">>
	The fox ears on <<his>> hat twitch.
<</if>>
"May I hold those for a moment?"
<br><br>

You oblige, handing them over. <<He>> digs around the shop, until <<he>> finds a strangely shaped magnifying glass. <<He>> examines the spectacles with it.
"Unusual prescription in these. Not quite for vision impairment. Like it's meant to correct something the human eye can't normally see." <<He>> holds them up to <<his>> eye, looking through them.
<br><br>

"Fascinating. Where did you find this?"
<br><br>

"There's this parlour," you explain. "A hookah parlour. I frequented it for a while, and saw some... interesting things when using it. I think I saw something I wasn't supposed to.
I heard someone break in and smash the hookah, but I didn't see it. When I opened my eyes, the old owner was gone. Those were <<if $per_npc.hookah.pronoun is "f">>her<<else>>his<</if>> glasses."
<br><br>

Gwylan listens intently to your story. <<He>> asks what kinds of things you saw while using the hookah, and you do your best to explain it all.
<br><br>

/* ToDo: Gwylan - Gwylan visits the parlour */
"So, you own it now?" <<he>> asks, and you nod. "<span class="green">I might just come visit you there sometime.</span> You've piqued my interest."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Islander
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("islander")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
<<set $daily.gwylan.traumaTalk to true>>
You show Gwylan the islander mask.
<br><br>

<<He>> runs <<his>> hand along the trim, up to the antlers. "This is good craftsmanship. Carved by hand. Not something done idly. How did you find this?"
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I... I made it, actually," you say shyly.
	<<case "bratty">>
		"Damn right it's good craftsmanship, because I made it," you say proudly.
	<<default>>
		"I'm glad you like it, because I carved it myself," you say.
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<His>> eyes widen. "You've got talent. Do you know what these symbols you've carved into it mean?"
<br><br>

<span class="purple">You don't remember carving any symbols into it.</span> Gwylan frowns. "That's alright, it's easy to become lost in your own work and do things without realising it."
<<He>> holds it up in the dim light. "It looks familiar. Like a design that was once common across the channel, a long time ago. What inspired you to make this?"
<br><br>

You tell <<him>> the long story of your time on the island. <<He>> listens intently through it all. <<He>> asks many questions about the islanders.
<br><br>

"So, part of that old culture is still alive," <<he>> says with a bright smile. "Thank you for telling me all of this.
The residents are the descendants of a group that split off from the mainland centuries ago. The head of a once-powerful noble family fled in exile with many trusted disciples, bringing with them a sacred artifact."
<br><br>

<<He>> stops, putting a finger to <<his>> chin. "What was it? A walking stick? A spear?"
<br><br>

/* ToDo: Gwylan - option to tell Gwylan about the spear? */

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Fox Mask
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("fox_mask")>><<set $gwylan.progress++>>
You show Gwylan the fox mask.
<br><br>

<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
	<<His>> fox ears twitch.
<<elseif _gwylanTF.ears is "revealed">>
	The fox ears on <<his>> hat twitch.
<</if>>
<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
	"Masquerade style. Often used in ritualistic celebrations. The mark of a sacrifice-to-be," <<he>> says grimly.
<<else>>
	"Masquerade style. Often used in ritualistic celebrations. Why do you have this?" <<he>> asks grimly.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I... went to a party with someone," you say. "It did seem ritualistic. There was a dance, and people with dog and elk masks, and—"
	<<case "bratty">>
		"I went to a weird party with someone," you say. "It seemed off. There was this dance, and people wearing different animal masks, and—"
	<<default>>
		"I went to a party with someone," you say. "It was ritualistic, I think. There was a dance, and everyone was wearing animal masks, and—"
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan's nails scrape the counter as <<his>> hands clench, leaving scratch marks in the old wood.
<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
	<<He>> stares through you for a moment. "You saw what happened, didn't you? You know that could have been you?"
<<elseif $worn.face.name is "fox mask">>
	"You were a part of it?"
<<else>>
	"You wore this?"
<</if>>
<br><br>

You nod.
<br><br>

<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
	<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
		<<set $daily.gwylan.locked to true>>
		There's something else behind <<his>> eyes now. "Yet you still gave them everything they wanted, despite knowing what they do to vulnerable people like you." <<npcincr Gwylan lust -20>><<npcincr Gwylan dom -2>><<llllust>><<lyearning>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> breathes out slowly. "You're better than this, even if you don't think you are. I hope you don't make the same mistake again."
	<<elseif $avery_fate is "saved">>
		<<He>> breathes out slowly. "And you still had it in your heart to save <<nnpc_him "Avery">>. Yours is a kind soul, indeed." <<He>> smiles at you.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> breathes out slowly. "It's okay. It's over now. Avery will never hurt anyone again."
	<</if>>
<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_sex")>>
	Gwylan marches around the counter, and hugs you. "Whoever you went with, never speak with them again," <<he>> commands. <<His>> hand holds the back of your head. <<He>> embraces you as if you'd vanish the moment <<he>> lets go.
	<br><br>

	Eventually, though, <<he>> does. "You're lucky to still be here," <<he>> says as <<he>> returns behind the counter. "You've been marked as a target by some very dangerous people. It goes so much deeper than you know."
<<else>>
	<<He>> takes a deep breath. "I would recommend you cut ties with whoever brought you there, for your own safety. You've been marked as a target by some very dangerous people."
	<<He>> leans in. "It goes so much deeper than you know. Please, dear, be careful."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Fedora
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("fedora")>>
You show Gwylan the fedora.
<br><br>

<<He>> takes it and turns it over. "The name fedora actually comes from a play. It used to be worn by women, but times change so quickly. It's a very fetching style." <<He>> puts it on your head, covering your eyes with a playful wink. "Wherever did you find it?"
<br><br>

"I was bartending," you say. You push the brim up to look at <<him>>. "I overheard some smugglers talking about their next job."
<br><br>

Gwylan runs a finger over a nearby shelf. "The shop has a strange sense of humour," <<he>> says. "Of course, fedoras have been associated with crime and alcohol for decades. I don't think it's worked to their benefit this time."
<br><br>

You hand the fedora back to <<him>>. <<He>> places it on a mannequin bust. <<if $hallucinations gte 2>>You think you see the mannequin wink at you, despite not having eyes.<</if>>
<br><br>

"Promise me you'll be careful," Gwylan adds. "Life is an adventure, and stories have power, but the criminals in this town are like spiders. They are waiting for you to step into their parlour."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("catsuit")>>
You show Gwylan the catsuit.
<br><br>

"Sleek," <<he>> says. "What mischief did you partake in to find this?"
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I was sneaking around at the docks, and I found it tucked away in one of the shipping containers," you say.
	<<case "bratty">>
		"I was getting into trouble at the docks and found it stashed in the back of a shipping container," you say.
	<<default>>
		"I was sneaking around at the docks and found it hidden in the back of a shipping container," you say.
<</switch>>
<br><br>

"Sticky fingers, huh?" Gwylan says. "I understand. When you find that perfect treasure hidden away somewhere, it's hard to pass it by. It's a slippery slope, though. One acquisition turns into another, then another, then the next thing you know, well..." <<He>> gestures at the items around you. "If you're not careful, you'll end up with quite a collection."
<br><br>

<<if $blackmoney gte 1000>>
	"Well," you say, "I <i>do</i> have quite the collection of stolen goods on me. Nothing special," you add when Gwylan gives you an inquisitive look, "just some valuables for selling on the black market."
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	"Would that be such a bad thing?" you ask.
	<br><br>

	"Of course not!" Gwylan gives you a wide smile. "But I'd hope you'd still find the time to stop by and see <i>this</i> collection."
<</if>>
<<He>> takes a seat. You blink. You don't recall seeing two chairs here before, but it's not the first time you've lost track of things in the shop.
<br><br>

As you take the seat opposite <<him>>, Gwylan leans forward and props <<his>> chin in the palm of <<his>> hand. "I'm curious, though," <<he>> says. "Sneaking around the docks like that... surely there were far more valuable treasures to steal. Monetarily, at least. But I think you can appreciate how the right piece of clothing is worth more than gold."
<br><br>

<<if $gwylanTalked.includes("chain_tunic")>>
	You think about Gwylan, hugging a cherished tunic to <<his>> chest.
<<else>>
	You glance at Gwylan's hat, and <<= ["fake", "revealed"].includes(_gwylanTF.ears) ? "the ears on it" : "the flowers adorning it">>.
<</if>>
It's a personal subject for <<him>>.
<br><br>

"I can't say I know of many people who would pick up some clothes they found shoved into a corner, let alone wear it. So, why did this one speak to you?"
<br><br>

<<link [[Say you met someone interesting there|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit 2]]>><<set $phase to "wren">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you were intrigued by the symbols nearby|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit Symbol]]>><<set $phase to "symbol">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you wanted to show off your figure|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit Figure]]>><<set $phase to "figure">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you thought it would come in handy|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit Useful]]>><<set $phase to "useful">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you just like free clothes|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit 2]]>><<set $phase to "free">><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Symbol
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("symbol")>>
<<set _seenLocations to []>>
	<<if $compound.symbol.includes("wraith")>>
	<<run _seenLocations.push("crates filled with pale creatures")>>
<</if>>
You do your best to describe it: the nested semi-circles, the branching tendrils, the three-cornered knot at the centre.
<<if $compound.symbol.length gt 1 or $gwylanSeen.includes("tattoos_intro")>>
	"I've seen that symbol before," you say.<<if $worn.neck.name is "stone pendant" and $compound.symbol.length gt 1>>"The full thing, not just the middle part, which looked like this." You hold up your stone pendant.<</if>>
	<<if $compound.symbol.includes("wraith")>>
		"I found it in the compound on Elk Street, on <<= _seenLocations.join(" and ")>>."
		<br><br>

		"Pale creatures?" Gwylan repeats. "Interesting." <<He>> absorbs this, then motions for you to continue.
		<br><br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $compound.symbol.includes("docks")>>
		"I've broken into other containers that had crates with this stamp on it. They had lots of complicated machinery parts in them," you say.
	<</if>>
	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("tattoos_intro") and $compound.symbol.length gt 1>>
		<<if $worn.neck.name is "stone pendant">>
			"And... that knot at the centre? It doesn't just match my pendant. I've seen it on your stomach before too."
		<<else>>
			"And... I've seen part of the symbol on you before. The middle bit looked like your tattoo."
		<</if>>
	<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("tattoos_intro")>>
		"On your stomach. The knot at the centre looked exactly like your tattoo<<if $worn.neck.name is "stone pendant">>, same as my pendant<</if>>."
	<<else>>
		"That's about it. It just felt like something noteworthy," you say.
	<</if>>
<<elseif $worn.neck.name is "stone pendant">>
	You hold up your stone pendant. "I haven't come across the whole symbol again, but the middle bit looked like this. It felt like something noteworthy."
<<else>>
	"I haven't come across it again, but it just felt like something noteworthy," you say.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Gwylan nods. "You said it was pink? I'd hazard a guess that those crates were intended for, or exported by, the Elk Street compound. It's not a symbol you see often these days," <<he>> says.
"The ribcage of a fallen god. An infinite pair of antlers, fracturing again, and again, and again. At its core, the seed of life. A knot with no beginning or end that can never be untied."
<<He>> looks directly at you.
"It's an old song. Some consider it part of the sacred geometry of the universe. I'm sure the compound has their own reasons for using it," <<he>> says.<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("tattoos_intro")>> <<He>> places <<his>> hands over <<his>> stomach and looks directly at you. "And I have my reasons for using this piece of it. Don't mistake the part for the whole."<</if>>
<<run $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("symbol")>>
<br><br>

A silence stretches between you. Gwylan breaks it first, suddenly chipper. "Well! I see why it left an impression on you."
<br><br>

You nod. "I didn't really think anything of it until now," you confess. "But yeah, I guess it did."

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit Symbol
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
You explain how you found the catsuit stashed among crates marked with a pink symbol.
<<if $compound.symbol.includes("catsuit")>>
	<<include "Gwylan Talk Symbol">>
<<else>>
	Gwylan looks intrigued, and asks you to describe it. "I didn't get a great look at it at the time," you admit. "I was a bit distracted. But I suppose it left an impression on me."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> nods thoughtfully. "Understandable. It could have been anything. A manufacturer's mark, a stamp from its sender, a company logo... although pink is an interesting colour of choice.
	Perhaps it was intended for, or sent by, one of the factories at the outskirts of town. Or the compound on Elk Street."
	<<He>> gives a small frown, then a slight shake of <<his>> head. When <<he>> speaks again, <<his>> voice is bright. "But there's no use speculating! I see why it piqued your curiosity."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit 2]]>><</link>>
<br>
:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Catsuit Figure
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
