	<<elseif $wrenSeen.includes("heist")>>
		You tell Gwylan how you initially served as a distraction while Wren picked pockets, then joined <<nnpc_him "Wren">> to crack the safe. <<if $wrenHeistCricketBall isnot undefined>><<He>> stifles a laugh when you tell <<him>> how you double-crossed your partner-in-crime.<</if>>
		<!-- note: this is THE (second) stupidest way to check for if PC stole the cricket ball, but currently it's how it works. we may want to use wrenSeen instead -->
		<br><br>
		When you describe the painting to <<him>>, <<his>> gaze sharpens, and <<he>> leans closer. "I've heard of that painting before. It belonged to Winter, didn't it?"
		<br><br>
