<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan nods along. "Some stories and legends have that curious property to them. If you immerse yourself in it, it's as though you're present in body and soul as well as mind."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Dance Studio
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("dance_studio")>>
You show Gwylan the swan lake tutu and accessories.
<br><br>

"Very pretty," Gwylan says, tracing a finger over one of the feathers. "It reminds me of a ballet I saw once, a long time ago. A tragic story." <<He>> pauses and cocks <<his>> head. "Or a romantic one? The ending changes, depending on the production." <<He>> glances at you. "When did these appear?"
<br><br>

<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"Well, I've been taking dancing lessons at a studio in town... I suppose I must have made a good impression, because the instructor asked me to perform at some parties. That's when the dress showed up."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"I've been making waves at the dance studio in town. This stuff showed up after the instructor pulled me aside and asked me to entertain at some parties."
	<<default>>
		"I've been taking dancing lessons at the studio in town, and I've gotten quite good at it. The instructor's asked me to work at a few parties around town. I found these in the shop shortly after."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan smiles. "That's fitting." <<He>> taps the swan lake tiara. "This story's been told countless times, but most adaptations agree that it begins with a party." <<He>> leans in closer to you. "So, how does your story end?"
<br><br>

<<set _danubeStats to V.moneyStats.find(stat => stat === "danubeDanceJob")>>
<<set _partyStats to V.moneyStats.find(stat => stat === "partyDanceJob")>>

You hesitate.
<<if $gwylanTalked.includes("temple_exorcist")>>
	"Happily," you finally say, giving a decisive nod. "I was able to rescue that member of Jordan's flock, after all. That was worth any bumps along the way."
	<br><br>

	"You freed a caged bird," Gwylan says, giving you a gentle smile. "I'd say it's worth it."
<<elseif _danubeStats?.earned gte 20000>>
	"Maybe a bit tragically," you say. You tell Gwylan about the lengths you had to go to to earn your pay, from handsy partygoers to the contraption they wheeled out for your debasement. Gwylan listens intently, brow furrowed.
<<elseif _danubeStats?.earnedCount gt 0 or _partyStats?.earnedCount gt 0>>
	"Well enough," you say. "I've made some decent money, so I can't really complain."
<<elseif getUnlockedSpecialSets().includes("temple_exorcist")>>
	"It... did not end the way I'd expected," you say. "It's a long story."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> tilts <<his>> head. "That so? I would love to hear more about it later."
<<else>>
	You admit that you've yet to follow through on a dance job. Gwylan looks disappointed, but doesn't press the matter.
<</if>>
<br><br>

As Gwylan goes to hang up the tutu once more, you speak. "Gwylan?" <<He>> gives an inquisitive hum and glances over <<his>> shoulder at you. "You said you saw the ballet once. How did it end for you?"
<br><br>

Gwylan taps <<his>> chin. "Well, it's been some time, but as I recall...

<<switch random(1,7)>>
	<<case 7>>The swan queen sacrificed herself. In their grief, her maidens destroyed the sorcerer, tearing him limb from limb."
	<<case 6>>The maiden remained a swan eternal. The curtain closed on her lover, alone in his grief."
	<<case 5>>The swan queen died in the prince's arms. He carried her to the lake, where they were reunited in death."
	<<case 4>>The prince clipped the sorcerer's wing, breaking the curse and liberating the swan maidens of the lake. For once, everyone lived."
	<<case 3>>The prince tore the crown from the swan queen's head. She died, and the waters of the lake rose to drown him."
	<<case 2>>The swan queen and her lover drowned at the hands of a witch."
	<<default>>The lovers chose to leap into the lake, where they drowned as one. Their sacrifice broke the enchantment, and they ascended to the heavens in apotheosis."
<</switch>>

<<He>> studies your face as you digest this. "But, of course, it's just a fairytale," <<he>> says.
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

