:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Jasper 3
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<switch $phase>>
	<<case 1>>
		"It looks like the tail of a fox," you say. "It comes to a point at the top, and the detail looks like the colour splitting."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> nods. "That is one part of it, yes. It's a bit of a trick, though."
	<<case 2>>
		"It looks like a rooster with a big tail," you say. "I can see the beak right there."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> nods. "That is one part of it, yes. It's a bit of a trick, though."
	<<case 3>>
		"It looks like a flame," you say. "The details make it look like its burning."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> nods. "That is one part of it, yes. It's a bit of a trick, though."
	<<case 4>>
		"It looks like the moon," you say. "The way the moon gets at the end of every month, if it were a crescent."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> blinks, turning it over in <<his>> hands. <<He>> tilts it slightly. "Huh. I suppose it can look like that." <<He>> smiles. "That wasn't the intention, but you've got a sharp mind to be able to see such things."
	<<default>>
		<<set $gwylan.progress++>>
		"It looks like a drop of blood. The negative space of the curve is meant to be a shining highlight."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> looks surprised, but starts slowly clapping. "Incredible. You're able to see past the components for what they are, and see their result instead. I'm very impressed." <<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><<gyearning>>
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<He>> hands it back to you. "It's many things. A fox tail, a rooster, and a flame, depending on how you look at it. It's alchemy. The rooster represents gold, as it greets the sun every morning, and the sun also represents gold.
The fox represents royal water; aqua regia. The flame is the reaction between them. Dissolve, heat, dissolve, repeat. The fox and rooster consume one another in an endless dance."
<br><br>

<<He>> gently holds your hands, and rotates the pendant in your palm. "Some called the result 'dragon's blood', for its intense red hue." <<He>> smiles.
"It was a bit of an inspiration piece for me. You're welcome to buy it, of course. I can always make more."
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

