:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers Listen
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
You shake off the compulsion, and focus on Gwylan's voice. It slowly fades back in.
<br><br>

"—crop rotation is important, even for flowers. Each type of plant needs different nutrients, and will take it all from the soil if permitted to.
Soil will replenish itself as minerals and natural fertiliser, like animal carcasses or droppings, decay nearby. The soil needs rest and nourishment, just like we do."
<br><br>

Gwylan runs <<his>> hand along the edges of the flower crown's petals. For some reason, it feels as though Gwylan is touching your ears the same way <<hes>> touching the petals.
<br><br>

<<He>> continues. "There's almost nothing I can't grow. Almost. Any colour of rose - by the way, did you know that you can use water with food colouring to change the colour of their petals? - anyways, they all grow fine, except for the pink ones.
No matter what I do, I can never get them to bloom, so I just pluck them early. Better to save nutrients for the others. Even trying to grow them in pink-dyed water just has them wither. Sometimes I think I'm cursed." <<He>> laughs, but looks sad for a moment.
<br><br>

<<He>> finally stops, and blushes. "Sorry. Thanks for listening to all of that. I don't get the chance to talk to many people about my flowers." <<tending 12>><<gggtending>>
<br><br>

You look down. The glowing flowers are gone. In their place is a single pristine pink rose.
<br><br>

<<set $plants_known.push("pink_rose")>>
<span class="gold">You can now grow <<icon "tending/pink_rose.png">> pink roses.</span>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers Touch
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $location to "meadow">><<set $outside to 1>><<set $phase to 0>>
<<headundress "gwylan_bloom">><<headwear "flower crown">>
You reach out and touch them gently. The bulbs shimmer and open up.
<br><br>

When you next blink, you're no longer in the forest shop. You're sitting in a meadow, with tall grass and flowers blowing in the breeze around you. The smells of nature soothe you into a trance, along with
<<if $seabird_lullaby gte 2>>
	<span class="teal">Seabird's Lullaby</span>
<<else>>
	a <span class="teal">faintly familiar melody</span>
<</if>>
being hummed behind you.
<br><br>

You don't turn to look. You know who it is, and you're safe with <<him>>. <<He>> places a crown of flowers on your head, and whispers something in your ear. <<He>> takes your hand, and kisses your cheek. <<llltrauma>><<trauma -50>>
<br><br>

<<His>> head rests against you. You've never felt so at peace. You close your eyes, content with your place in the world.
<br><br>

Something pushes you. An alien presence pulling you downwards. You're sinking into the flowers, yet the ground gets no closer. No voice speaks, yet a command is made.
<br><br>

<span class="nextLinkWitch"><<link [[All dreams must end. Wake up.|Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers End]]>><</link>></span>
<br>
<<link [[Resist|Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers Resist]]>><<stress 3>><</link>><<gstress>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers Resist
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $phase++>>
<<switch $phase>>
	<<case 1>><span class="narration">Close your eyes, and imagine it with me.</span>
	<<case 2>><span class="narration">Push away everything else, even if just for a moment. Imagine the breeze. It's refreshing, like a cold drink on a hot day.</span>
	<<case 3>><span class="narration">The wind carries pollen like birdsong. It serves a similar purpose, seeking out a mate.</span>
	<<case 4>><span class="narration">It's comforting, don't you think? Flowers are a lot like us.</span>
	<<case 5>><span class="narration">They need interaction to thrive, sometimes in ways we can't understand. But, talking to them helps them grow, too.</span>
	<<case 6>><span class="narration">Don't resist the wind. Plants know to bend, lest they snap at the stem. Let it carry you in its gentle dance.</span>
	<<case 7>><span class="narration">Yet, your roots remain firm. The ground beneath you is life itself. It nourishes you, so long as you aren't avaricious. If you take too much, the soil will become depleted and die.</span>
	<<case 8>><span class="narration">We all share this earth, yet so many are cruel to it. Polluting and depleting everything, leaving poison in our wake. Any damage we cause to the world is a burden we'll share, whether we like it or not.</span>
	<<default>>
<</switch>>
<<if $phase lt 8>>
	<br><br>

	You keep your eyes shut.
<</if>>
