:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Flowers End
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $location to "forest_shop">><<set $outside to 0>>
<<headruined true>><<storeonhead "gwylan_bloom">>
<<if $phase gte 9>>
	You keep your eyes shut. You don't know how much time passes, but the smells of the meadow fade. You don't feel the wind on your skin anymore. The comfort, and the pain, both fade away.
	All that remains is Gwylan's voice. You slowly open your eyes when you're sure it's over.
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	You heed the command, and open your eyes.
<</if>>
You're back in the forest shop.
<br><br>

Gwylan runs <<his>> hand along the edges of the flower crown's petals. For some reason, it feels as though Gwylan is touching your ears the same way <<hes>> touching the petals.
"—and, no matter what I do, I can never get the pink ones to bloom, so I just pluck them early. Better to save the nutrients for the other roses. Sometimes I think it's a curse."
<br><br>

<<He>> looks up and smiles at you, but it's immediately replaced by a look of concern. "Oh, are you alright? You look irritated."
<br><br>

You shake off the question. A sense of bliss just out of reach taunts you, but fades just as quickly. "Well, thanks for listening to all of that. I don't get the chance to talk to many people about my flowers."
<<tending 6>><<ggtending>>
<br><br>

The three glowing blooms are gone. In their place is one pristine pink rose.
<br><br>

<<set $plants_known.push("pink_rose")>>
<span class="gold">You can now grow <<icon "tending/pink_rose.png">> pink roses.</span>
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

Your eyes flutter open.
<br><br>

You're still in the meadow. The flowers have all bloomed beautifully. A mousy-haired <<personsimple>> sits in front of you, holding both of your hands and smiling. <<He>> looks a lot like Gwylan, but a bit older.
<br><br>

"I didn't fall asleep," your voice says. "But I wouldn't mind falling asleep with you."
<br><br>

<<He>> giggles, and you help <<him>> stand. <<His>> smile fades. "Are you crying?" <<He>> caresses your face, wiping away your tears. "What's wrong, love?" <<llpain>>
<br><br>

"I... don't remember," your voice answers.
<br><br>

<<link [[Walk|Gwylan Memory Bloom Roses]]>><<set $pain to 0>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Roses
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<wearProp "pink rose basket">>

The two of you continue your walk. There's no one else here. The presence attempting to push you out is gone.
<br><br>

A look of awe crosses <<his>> face. "Look over there!" <<He>> points to something in the distance. A bramble dotted with countless pink flowers. <<He>> begins running towards it, and you run with <<him>>.
<br><br>

"I hardly ever see pink roses in the wild," <<he>> says as <<he>> starts picking a few. "You've seen my attempts to grow them at home. No matter what I do, they never bloom."
<<He>> begins picking them. "A little help, love?"
<br><br>

You help <<him>> pick the roses, leaving any that have yet to bloom. <<tending 6>><<ggtending>>
<br><br>

"Maybe we're cursed," <<he>> muses.
<<if $settings.pregnancySpeechEnabled and playerCanBreedWith("Gwylan")>>
	"Pink roses represent love and fertility. Maybe that's why we can't conceive."
<<else>>
	"Pink roses represent the longevity of love through sickness and health. I'm sickly so often, and yet you love me all the same."
<</if>>
<<He>> cautiously holds out a bunch of roses to you, as if <<hes>> afraid they'll wilt in <<his>> hands. Despite the slight bitterness of <<his>> comment, <<hes>> smiling widely again.
<br><br>

"Want to see a magic trick? Put those down for a moment."
<br><br>

You nod, and <<he>> takes both of your hands. <<He>> cups them into a ball, and you suddenly feel a pinprick against your skin. You open your hands, now holding one last rose. "Ta-da!"
<br><br>

You start clapping for <<him>>, but <<he>> frowns and grabs your wrists. <<He>> looks at the palm of your right hand, <span class="red">now impaled by three small thorns</span>. "Oh, apologies, love. My trick inflicted a wound," <<he>> says dramatically, plucking out the thorns.
"I'll be sure to care for your injury when we return home." <<gpain>>
<br><br>

You take the opportunity to pay <<him>> back. "No wound will slow me down," your voice responds just as dramatically. You hold <<his>> wrist, and twirl <<him>>.
<br><br>

<<link [[Dance|Gwylan Memory Bloom Petals]]>><<handheldon>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Petals
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
You dance between the flowers as the wind picks up. <<He>> giggles all the while.
<br><br>

You waltz to a rhythm only the two of you can hear. Petals blow all around you, as if the meadow itself was dancing along with you.
<br><br>

The wind dies down, and your dance slows along with it, until you're merely shuffling side to side while embracing. Dark clouds begin to gather in the distance.
<br><br>

<<He>> looks up to you with love in <<his>> eyes. It's briefly cut off as <<he>> starts coughing into <<his>> arm.
<br><br>

<<He>> takes a deep breath as it subsides. "I'm tired," <<he>> says. "Why don't we head home, and I'll clean up your hand." Your faces get closer.
<br><br>

<<if $settings.pregnancySpeechEnabled and playerCanBreedWith("Gwylan")>>
	"After that... <span class="lewd">why don't we try breaking this curse?</span>" <<he>> whispers with a sly smile.
<<else>>
	"After that... <span class="lewd">we can love each other, through sickness and through health,</span>" <<he>> whispers with a sly smile.
<</if>>
Your lips nearly meet.
<br><br>

<<link [[Kiss <<him>>|Gwylan Memory Bloom Thorns]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Thorns
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<canvas-model-override "mouth" "neutral">>
<<set Weather.set("heavyPrecipitation", true, 5)>>
<span class="red">A flash of lightning and the crash of thunder interrupts your moment of love. <<He>> falls backwards. The pink roses catch <<him>> in their thorny embrace.</span>
<br><br>

<<He>> vanishes, as if swallowed by the earth itself.
<br><br>

You catch yourself before you land face-first in the thorns, but <<he>> is gone.
<br><br>

The roses wilt before your eyes. The thorns grow long and cruel, each one dripping red. They grow towards you, trying to ensnare you.
<br><br>

You push yourself away, and look around in desperation. You scream <<his>> name. The howling wind is your only answer.
<br><br>

<<link [[Find <<him>>|Gwylan Memory Bloom Wilt]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Wilt
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $location to "forest">><<tearup>><<canvas-model-override "frown">>
You wander, searching for <<him>>. The trees obscure your vision.
<br><br>

You yell <<his>> name. The wind drowns out your cries.
<br><br>

You run to cover more ground. The rain weighs heavy on you.
<br><br>

You fall to your knees. The earth provides no comfort.
<br><br>

You scream in anguish. The sky screams with you.
<br><br>

You clutch at your head. The flower crown rots away in your grip.
<br><br>

<<link [[...|Gwylan Memory Bloom Rot]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Rot
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $location to "forest_shop">><<set $outside to 0>>
If you stay here, you'll rot away and vanish, too.
<br><br>

Right now, you wouldn't mind. But you know that's foolish. You pick yourself up, and walk home.
<br><br>

It's empty. You prayed it wouldn't be.
<br><br>

"I'm home," <<he>> says to nobody, long after you're gone.
<br><br>

<span class="nextLinkWitch"><<link [[Wake up.|Gwylan Memory Bloom Perennial]]>><<pass 15>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Gwylan Memory Bloom Perennial
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $location to "forest_shop">><<set $outside to 0>><<set $daily.gwylan.noTalk to true>>
<<canvas-model-override "clear">><<headruined true>><<storeonhead "gwylan_bloom">><<tearup>>
You open your eyes.
<br><br>

You're back in the forest shop. You and Gwylan are holding each other's hands tightly. <<takeHandholdingVirginity "Gwylan" `(V.gwylanSeen.includes("yearning") ? "romantic" : "consensual")`>>
<br><br>

<span class="red">The flower crown lays crushed in your shared grip.</span> Your ears are ringing.
<br><br>

"...and, no matter what I do, I... I can never get the pink ones to bloom, so I just pluck them early," <<he>> says absently. Tears are running down <<his>> face.
<br><br>

"Why are you crying?" <<he>> says to you. <<He>> wipes the tears from your eyes, before wiping <<his>> own face. "Why... am <i>I</i> crying?"
<<He>> looks down at the crushed flower crown in confusion. "I... can't remember," you both say in unison.
<br><br>

<<He>> sniffles. "I'm sorry. I don't feel well. Thank you for spending time with me, but I'm... I need to think." <<He>> slowly retreats through a dark doorway, and vanishes. <<npcincr Gwylan dom 10>><<gggyearning>>
<br><br>

You place the ruined flower crown back. One of the flowers comes loose.
<br><br>

<span class="pink">A pink rose.</span> Pristine, despite the rest of the crown being ruined. As you inspect it, you notice three red pinpricks in your right palm.
<br><br>

<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("pink_rose")>>
<<set $plants_known.push("pink_rose")>>
<span class="gold">You can now grow <<icon "tending/pink_rose.png">> pink roses.</span>
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Forest Shop Entrance]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Transformation
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set _tf to checkTFparts()>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("transformation")>>
<<set _jasper to $gwylanTalked.includes("jasper") or $worn.neck.name is "jasper pendant">>
<<set $daily.gwylan.traumaTalk to true>>
You walk around the shop with Gwylan, collecting the eerie items.
<br><br>

You place them all on the counter. The cow bell, the feathered accessories, and the spirit mask. You think for a moment, and bring over the fake wings from the succubus outfit<<if _jasper>> and the jasper pendant<</if>>, too.
<br><br>

"Interesting combination of items," Gwylan says. "What made you pick these out as a group?"
<br><br>

<<set _tfPartList to Object.keys(_tf)>>
<<set _tfPartSay to []>>
<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("angelWings", "fallenAngelWings", "demonWings", "birdWings")>>
	<<set _tfPartSay.push("wings")>>
<</if>>
<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("angelHalo", "fallenAngelHalo")>>
	<<set _tfPartSay.push("halo")>>
<</if>>
<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("cowHorns", "demonHorns")>>
	<<set _tfPartSay.push("horns")>>
<</if>>
<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("wolfTail", "catTail", "cowTail", "birdTail", "foxTail", "demonTail")>>
	<<set _tfPartSay.push("tail")>>
<</if>>
<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("wolfEars", "catEars", "cowEars", "foxEars")>>
	<<set _tfPartSay.push("ears")>>
<</if>>

<<if _tfPartSay.length>>
	<<set _tfPartsPlural to _tfPartSay.length is 1 and _tfPartSay.includesAny("halo", "tail") ? false : true>>
	"They remind me of..." You gesture to your <<print formatList(_tfPartSay)>>.
	<<if !_tfPartsPlural>>
		"This."
	<<elseif _tfPartSay.length gte 3>>
		"All of this."
	<<else>>
		"These."
	<</if>>
	<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("foxEars", "foxTail")>>
		You point to the spirit mask<<if _jasper>> and jasper pendant<</if>>. "<<= _jasper ? "Those ones" : "This one">> especially."
		<<if $worn.head.name is "spirit mask" or $worn.neck.name is "jasper pendant">>
			<<if $worn.head.name is "spirit mask" and $worn.neck.name is "jasper pendant">>
				You point to the matching ones on your head and around your neck for emphasis.
			<<elseif $worn.head.name is "spirit mask">>
				You point to the matching one on your head for emphasis.
			<<elseif $worn.neck.name is "jasper pendant">>
				You point to the matching one around your neck for emphasis.
			<</if>>
		<</if>>
		<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("demonWings", "demonTail", "demonHorns")>>
			Your eyes drift over to the succubus costume. "That one too, but not in the same way."
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _tfPartList.includesAny("cowEars", "cowHorns", "cowTail")>>
		You point to the cow bell. "That one especially."
		<<if $worn.neck.name is "cow bell">>
			You point to the matching one around your neck for emphasis.
		<</if>>
		<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("demonWings", "demonTail", "demonHorns")>>
			Your eyes drift over to the succubus costume. "That one too, but not in the same way."
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _tfPartList.includesAny("birdWings", "birdTail")>>
		You point to the feathered hair clip and necklace. "Those ones especially."
		<<if $worn.head.name is "feathered hair clip" and $worn.neck.name is "feather necklace">>
			You point to the matching ones on your head and around your neck for emphasis.
		<<elseif $worn.head.name is "feathered hair clip">>
			You point to the matching one on your head for emphasis.
		<<elseif $worn.neck.name is "feather necklace">>
			You point to the matching one around your neck for emphasis.
		<</if>>
		<<if _tfPartList.includesAny("demonWings", "demonTail", "demonHorns")>>
			Your eyes drift over to the succubus costume. "That one too, but not in the same way."
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _tfPartList.includesAny("demonWings", "demonTail", "demonHorns")>>
		You point to the succubus costume. "That one especially. Although, it feels different to the others."
	<<else>>
		You pause. "Not directly, but like it's something distantly related."
		<<if $worn.neck.type.includes("eerie")>>
			You point to your $worn.neck.name. "Similar to this."
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan walks around you, inspecting your <<if _tfPartSay.length gte 2>>unusual parts<<else>><<print _tfPartSay[0]>><</if>>.
	"Even if <<if _tfPartsPlural>>they were<<else>>it was<</if>> real, most people wouldn't believe it.
	Still, you're bold, showing <<if _tfPartsPlural>>these<<else>>this<</if>> off so freely. Lecherous types might find you more appealing."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> smiles and crosses <<his>> arms. "Some accessories help contribute to how you express your inner self, like these ones that you've found.
	They can ease the pain of the mind ripping through skin and bone to make it better fit its self-image.
	<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
		I still prefer to keep mine hidden." <<His>> tail swishes. "Not from you, though. I trust you.
	<</if>>
	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("hypnosis_peace")>>
		Let me know if you need help coming to peace with it all again."
	<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("player_tf")>>
		Don't forget about my offer, if you find yourself doubting or rejecting yourself."
	<<else>>
		If you ever start doubting your inner self... <span class="blue">come talk to me</span>. I'll help you take care of it."
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	"I don't know," you confess. "They all give off a strange feeling."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan walks around you, inspecting you. "There are parts of us, our personality, our being, that usually only exist on the inside," <<he>> explains.
	"Perhaps, if belief holds true, those inner parts can manifest on the outside. Such expression, when the mind rips through skin and bone, can be painful."
	<br><br>

	<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
		<<His>> tail swishes. "Some still feel the need to hide it from everyone, except for their most trusted friends."
	<</if>>
	<<He>> places <<his>> hand on your shoulder and brings <<his>> head to your ear.
	<<if !$settings.transformAnimalEnabled>>
		"None of it will be real. Not unless you start believing in it," <<he>> whispers. "If you ever do, <span class="blue">come talk to me</span>. I know how to help."
	<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("player_tf")>>
		"My offer still stands, even if you're hiding your inner self right now," <<he>> whispers.
	<<else>>
		"If you begin manifesting your inner self, and you're unsure or confused about it, <span class="blue">come talk to me</span>. I know how to help," <<he>> whispers.
	<</if>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("player_tf")>>
<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Mask
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("mask")>>
<<set _nobody to $awarelevel gte 3 and _saveLoaded ? "nobody" : "Gwylan">>
<<if _nobody is "nobody">>
	<<run localStorage.setItem("gwylanTalk", "nobody")>>
<</if>>
<<set $daily.gwylan.traumaTalk to true>>
You show <<= _nobody>> the fox mask and the islander mask, although you're not sure what made you pick out the two of them in particular.
<br><br>

<<if _nobody is "Gwylan">>
	"The elk and the fox," <<he>> says. "A noble prey animal, and an unassuming but mischievous predator. Masks for each, to conceal identity."
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	Nobody answers.
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<= _nobody.toUpperFirst()>> walks over to a window.

<<if _nobody is "Gwylan">>
	"Those two animals were an important part of a local religion in more pagan times of worship, along with the hound, serpent, <<if $awarelevel gte 3>><span class="erase-from-history">whale, </span><</if>>rat, and bird. The cloister has largely done away with that symbolism."
	<br><br>

	"Elk were seen as a perfect form to aspire to, because of their antlers. Those with three prongs on each antler, specifically. After a religious schism, many instead saw them as unclean beasts in need of extermination."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> turns to you with an empty look on <<his>> face. "Then there's the fox. The treasured prey for games of the hunt, run by those that poison the world."
	<<He>> scowls. "The most favoured of victims. The hounds bray at the heels of the elk for scraps of the kill, and the rats eat what remains."
	<br><br>

	"I find this all very strange, as elk supposedly went extinct in this country several millennia ago. Regardless, here they are, a religious symbol. Protected by some, overhunted by others, and making meals of foxes despite being herbivores."
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	<br><br>

	Nobody turns to you with an empty face.
	<br><br>

	Nobody finds this all very strange.
	<br><br>
<</if>>

"What about the bird?" you ask.
<br><br>

<<if _nobody is "Gwylan">>
	<<He>> smiles. "Supposedly, the bird is above it all. Yet, when all is said and done, they fly down to pick at the same scraps as the rats.
	If they're not the ones hunting down and feeding the foxes to their young themselves."
	The tone of <<his>> voice tells you that this probably isn't part of the original symbology.
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	Nobody smiles. This isn't part.
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<if $awarelevel gte 3 and !_saveLoaded>>
	"And what about the whale?" you ask.
	<br><br>

	Gwylan's head tilts. "I... didn't mention a whale," <<he>> says.
	<br><br>

	"Yes you did, I..." Your head feels fuzzy. Try as you might, you can't remember anything about a whale.
	<br><br>

	"Shhhhh. This is better for us both. Please. It's dangerous." Gwylan rubs the top of your head. It comforts you.
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<elseif _nobody is "nobody">>
	<<pass 3 hours>><<pass 33>><<set $control to 0>><<trauma 333>>
	<<set $daily.gwylan.noTalk to true>><<gwylanNobody 1>>
	"Didn't we just have this conversation?" you ask nobody.
	<br><br>

	"<span class="witch-gone">I'm sorry. Listen, this is important. I'll be back soon, don't be scared, I just... I... I feel sick</span>," nobody answers.
	<br><br>

	The forest shop is empty and dark. Nobody rubs the top of your head. It comforts you. <<awareness -50>><<lllawareness>>
	<br><br>

	<<link [[...|Forest Shop Entrance]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	<<gwylanOptions>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Fox
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("fox")>>
You look at the fox mask, spirit mask, shrine maiden robes, and jasper pendant. You think about what Gwylan has said about them, and about foxes.
<br><br>

<<if _gwylanTF.known>>
	You flick Gwylan's fox ears. "I can't believe you were able to hide it from me for so long. It seems so obvious now," you say.
	<br><br>

	Gwylan pouts and crosses <<his>> arms. "Shush. Most people aren't as curious as you. That's why I like you."
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<else>>
	"You sure do like foxes," you say. "You talk about them a lot."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> blushes and stammers for a moment. "I-I just think they're cute," <<he>> manages. "They're relatable."
	<<if $fox gte 6>>
		<<He>> pinches your cheek. "Like you."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $settings.transformAnimalEnabled and Object.values(_gwylanTF).includesAny("fake", "revealed") and $gwylanSeen.includes("hat_found")>>
		You remember what you saw.
		<<if ["fake", "revealed"].includes(_gwylanTF.tail)>>
			The tail.
		<</if>>
		<<if ["fake", "revealed"].includes(_gwylanTF.fangs)>>
			<<His>> teeth.
		<</if>>
		<<if ["fake", "revealed"].includes(_gwylanTF.ears)>>
			Those ears on <<his>> hat.
		<</if>>
		It might have been nothing, but what if it wasn't?
		<br><br>

		<<link [[Press|Gwylan Talk Clothes Fox 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
		<br>
		<<link [[Drop it|Gwylan Talk Clothes Fox 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
		<br>
	<<else>>
		You shrug, and decide not to press any further. Still, you can't shake the feeling that <<hes>> hiding something.
		<br><br>

		<<gwylanOptions>>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Fox 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	"Just how relatable?" you ask, leaning in. "I always wondered why you wear that big hat, with the ears. Are you hiding something?" You reach up for Gwylan's head.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> backs away, covering it. "I'm afraid I don't know what you're talking about," <<he>> says.
	<br><br>

	<span class="blue">It's obvious now.</span>
	<br><br>

	"You talked about how the inner self can show up on the outside.
	<<if $fox gte 6>>
		You're just like me, aren't you? You're a fox, too."
	<<else>>
		You were talking about yourself, too, weren't you?"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<span class="teal"><<His>> eyes widen slightly.</span>
	<br><br>

	"No, I just like to dress up, I..." <<He>> pauses, and takes a deep breath. <<He>> looks you up and down, and after a long moment, seems to come to a decision. "Very well. <span class="green">You're clever.</span>"
	<br><br>

	<<He>> ducks under the counter, and starts to rummage around for something.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Next|Gwylan Talk TF Revealed]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	You don't press it any further. It was surely nothing.
	<br><br>

	<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
	<<gwylanOptions>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Familiar Collar
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set _tf to checkTFparts()>><<set $daily.gwylan.clothesTalk++>>
<<set $gwylanTalked.pushUnique("familiar_collar")>>

<<if $worn.neck.name is "familiar collar">>
	<<if $worn.neck.cursed is 1 and $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 4>>
		<<hypnosisText "You lean forward and proudly show Gwylan your familiar collar.">> <<He>> giggles and pets you. "<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "good">>." <<trauma -1>><<ltrauma>>
	<<else>>
		You lean forward and show Gwylan your familiar collar. <<He>> giggles and pets you. "<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "good">>."
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	You hold out the familiar collar to Gwylan. <<He>> giggles. "I think it'd look better if you were wearing it, <<pcPetname "Gwylan">>."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> rubs the gold heart.
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("player_tf")>>
	"There's another effect this will have on you. <span class="blue">It will preserve the more bestial side of your inner self, no matter what manifestation it takes.</span>"
<<else>>
	"There's another effect this collar can have on you. Should you find your inner self expressing beast-like qualities, this collar will preserve them. <span class="blue">Any of them.</span>"
<</if>>
<<He>> slowly strokes your hair. "Only the best to keep my darling pet happy."
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Talk Clothes Forgot
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<unset $gwylanPassTime>>
<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I don't remember, sorry," you say.
	<<case "bratty">>
		"I don't know, it's impossible to remember of all this," you say.
	<<default>>
		"I don't remember," you say. "Sorry."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

<<He>> tilts <<his>> head.
<<if $gwylanTalked.length gte 10>>
	"You're such a tease. Tell me when you do! Your stories are always so interesting."
<<else>>
	"Well, come back and tell me if you do."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>
